$PROB RUN# 100 - fit of Phase I data base model $INPUT C NUM ID TIME SEQ CMT EVID AMT DV AGE WT HT EGFR ALB BMI SEX AAG SCR AST ALT CP TAFD TAD LDOS MDV BLQ PHASE
$DATA ../../../data/derived/analysis3.csv IGNORE=@ IGNORE=(BLQ.EQ.1)
$SUBROUTINE ADVAN2 TRANS2
$PK
;log transformed PK parms
KA = EXP(THETA(1)+ETA(1)) V = EXP(THETA(2)+ETA(2)) CL = EXP(THETA(3)+ETA(3))
S2 = V/1000 ; dose in mcg, conc in mcg/mL
$ERROR IPRED = F
Y=IPRED*(1+EPS(1))
$THETA ; log values (-0.69) ; 1 KA (1/hr) - 1.5 (3.5) ; 2 V2 (L) - 60 (1) ; 3 CL (L/hr) - 3.5
$OMEGA BLOCK(3) 0.2 ;ETA(KA) 0.01 0.2 ;ETA(V) 0.01 0.01 0.2 ;ETA(CL)
$SIGMA 0.05 ; 1 pro error
$EST MAXEVAL=9999 METHOD=1 INTER SIGL=9 NSIG=3 PRINT=1 RANMETHOD=P MSFO=./100.msf $COV PRINT=E RANMETHOD=P $TABLE NUM IPRED NPDE CWRES NOPRINT ONEHEADER RANMETHOD=P FILE=100.tab $TABLE NUM CL V KA ETAS(1:LAST) NOAPPEND NOPRINT ONEHEADER FILE=100par.tab
